Hi.

This is a detailed guide to each file that make up the Uptown Film website.

The files are rooted here in Github. But the files are deployed in Vercel. While the email newsletter are managed in Mailchimp.

Folders:

ğŸ”´ api: This folder keeps the [subscribe.js] file. Which sets up the backend of the newsletter. This file is responsible for connecting the page to Mail Chimp. Sending the name and email put in the newsletter
to the Mailchimp email manager;
 
ğŸ”´ public: This folder keeps all the graphics. The photos, gifs, logos and icons. The file [sitemap.xml] exists to host Search Engine Optimization terms that
can help push the website to the front page search engines;

ğŸ”´ src: This folder hosts the core of the entire website.[App.jsx] is the body of this webapplication, [FeaturePage.jsx] is the additional page, [Main.jsx] is a map that tells the route for each file,
[index.css] imports TailWind frameworks used for better costumization;
  ğŸ”´ assets: here you find [Data.js] the one file responsible for the pages translation into English or Arabic;
    ğŸ”´components: This folder maintains all the core components of the website. [Home.jsx], [About.jsx] and [FeaturedPresentation.jsx] are sections within the home page.
      [Modal.jsx] this file allows the styling of the newsteller modal
       to not interfere with the styling of the other components. [Navbar.jsx] is the navigation bar. [Newsletter.jsx] is the front-end component of the newsletter funtion while,
         [NewsletterModal.jsx] is the pop up menu that pops up
          when you click on the newsletter button. And [SharedStyle.css] is the style of the page shared across components, meaning, the colors, hover effects, fonts, etc.

ğŸ”´ The root files: [index.html] is the skeleton of the page, it tells the web browser this is a webpage.
  [package.json] this is where we call upon the frameworks and their funtions that make it so the page is rendered as a React/Vite application.
   [package-lock.json] is a continuation of that file and where those frameworks and their functions are installed.
    [post.config.js] - [tailwind.config.js] - [vercel.json] - [vite.config.js] all these files are additional configurations that
     tell the Tailwind and Vite framework, as well as the Vercel platform, where to look for files.


